The pretext that these sanctions have provided is that Zimbabwe is an international criminal nation. However, it is the present day Britain that leads the world as far as human rights abuses and criminal activities are concerned. The lawmakers of Zimbabwe spoke to the House of Commons on the 27th of June, 1929 calling for an end to racial discrimination in Britain and its Commonwealth. What a joke! The white man never likes to be told the truth because they never believe in it.

Tax on cash in Zimbabwe

The Economic Sanctions imposed on Zimbabwe by the leaders of the United Kingdom were then followed by a pervasive inflationary witch-hunt. Not only have the people of Zimbabwe suffered unemployment and long queues to buy basic commodities, fuel and stable water, but businesses will also go bankrupt. The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has given its presentation on what it says is responsible for the devastating economic downturn. It has however, blamed President Robert Mugabe and his party, but the results were evident on the night of the 27th of December1999, when the government under the newly established Movement for Democratic Change (MDC) won the majority votes and President Robert Mugabe who had been in the presidency for so many times before that very night was announced by the Zimbabwe Electoral Commission’s (ZEC) Chief Elections Officer, Professor Paul Zimunya as the President elect.The ZEC
